headline: Cisco Is Feeling the Pressure of Higher Memory Costs. The Stock Is Tumbling.
summary: Cisco Systems  stock was dropping hard as Wall Street focused on how rising memory costs are affecting its profit margins.  Cisco reported better-than-expected fiscal second-quarter earnings and revenue after the stock market closed on Wednesday.  Shares closed at a record high in December, the first time since March 27, 2000, right before Cisco got slammed as the internet bubble popped.
